<%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>
    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html lang="en">

    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>FAQs</title>
        <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/22d10a4416.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
        <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
            integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
    </head>
    <style>
        h1 {
            margin-top: 60px;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .accordian {
            max-width: 65%;
            padding: 4px 16px;
            line-height: 1.6rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #666;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            cursor: pointer;

        }

        .contain {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .accordian.active {
            border: none;
            background-color: #f7f7f7;
        }

        .accordian:hover {
            background-color: #f7f7f7;
        }

        .question {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .question>p {
            padding-top: 10px;
        }

        .icon {
            margin-right: 16px;
            transition: transform 0.2s;
        }

        .icon.active {
            transform: rotate(-180deg);
        }

        .answer {
            color: #666;
            max-height: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: max-height 0.2s;
        }

        @media(max-width: 500px) {
            h1 {
                font-size: 1.4rem;
            }
        }
    </style>

    <body>
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <div class="contain">
            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>What is Check UV?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>Check UV shows the UV data,sun positions,suntimes and personal skintype information based on the
                        given location and time of the user and thus helps you protect yourself from sunburns. </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>How to use this website?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>First you need to know your <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/320639">Skin
                            Type</a>.Then,you simply need to enter your location,date and time and the website will
                        automatically show UV data based on the information given.Thus,you can choose a specific time of
                        the day while going out to prevent sunburns.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>What is Skin Type and how to find it for mine?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>The Fitzpatrick skin type system can help predict who is at risk of sunburn by categorizing skin
                        according to how much melanin is present.For more information check out this <a
                            href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/320639">website.</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>How much UV is harmful for humans?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>A UV index of 4 or higher is considered harmful to human health, especially with prolonged
                        exposure. Excessive exposure can lead to skin aging, DNA damage, eye cataracts, and immune
                        system suppression, making sun protection crucial in high UV conditions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>What measures to take if I got a sunburn?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>Avoid Further Exposure,Cool the Affected Area,Take Cool Baths or Showers,Apply Cold
                        Compresses,Moisturize Your Skin,Use Aloe Vera Gel,Apply Moisturizers,Stay Hydrated,Drink Plenty
                        of Water,Over-the-Counter Pain Relievers and consult a healthcare professional in case of severe
                        symptoms.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>In my city,Safe Exposure Time shows NULL what to do?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>Factors like cloud cover, altitude, and reflective surfaces (e.g., snow or water) can influence
                        the UV intensity.Safe exposure time is only relevant when the sun is out, so during nighttime
                        hours or in winter at high latitudes, UV radiation might be negligible, leading to a null or
                        irrelevant result.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordian container">
                <div class="question">
                    <p>Is the data in website authentic?</p>
                    <i class="icon fa-solid fa-caret-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>The data is taken from well-checked and revised API named <a
                            href="https://www.openuv.io/dashboard">OpenUV API</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <script>
            const accordians = document.querySelectorAll('.accordian');
            accordians.forEach(accordian => {
                const icon = accordian.querySelector('.icon');
                const answer = accordian.querySelector('.answer');

                accordian.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    if (icon.classList.contains('active')) {
                        icon.classList.remove('active');
                        answer.style.maxHeight = null;
                        accordian.classList.remove('active');
                    } else {
                        icon.classList.add('active');
                        answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
                        accordian.classList.add('active');
                    }

                });
            });
        </script>
    </body>

    </html>
    <%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>